<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="422" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[135,760,704,1121]" pageId="9" pageNumber="422">
Remarks. 
<bibRefCitation author="SPINOLA, M." bookContentInfo="383 p." box="[294,484,922,942]" journalOrPublisher="Genoa, Yves Graviers" pageId="9" pageNumber="422" refId="ref8394" refString="SPINOLA, M. 1837. Essai sur les genres d'insectes appartenants a l'ordre des Hemipteres, Lin. ou Rhyngotes, Fab. et a la section des Heteropteres, Dufour. Genoa, Yves Graviers, 383 p." title="Essai sur les genres d'insectes appartenants a l'ordre des Hemipteres, Lin. ou Rhyngotes, Fab. et a la section des Heteropteres, Dufour" type="book" year="1837">SPINOLA (1837: 287)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the male of the species was unknown. He certainly misinterpreted the sex of the specimens. The male keeping the pygophore in the abdomen is here designated 
<typeStatus box="[370,497,1012,1031]" pageId="9" pageNumber="422">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
, considering there are two specimens under the same green label and to assign a single specimen of this species as the name-bearer.
</paragraph>
